EIOPA governance requirements for fit and proper persons include the following:

*   **Fit Requirements:** National competent authorities should ensure undertakings ensure that persons who have other key functions or effectively run the undertaking (including members of the management, supervisory, or administrative body) are "fit" [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0012__guideline-11-fit-requirements]. This involves considering allocated duties to ensure a professional manner of oversight and management through a diversity of relevant experience, knowledge, and qualifications [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0012__guideline-11-fit-requirements]. Collectively, members of the supervisory, management, or administrative body must possess appropriate knowledge, experience, and qualification in:
    *   Financial and insurance markets [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0012__guideline-11-fit-requirements];
    *   Business model and business strategy [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0012__guideline-11-fit-requirements];
    *   Requirements and regulatory framework [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0012__guideline-11-fit-requirements];
    *   System of governance [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0012__guideline-11-fit-requirements];
    *   Actuarial and financial analysis [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0012__guideline-11-fit-requirements].
*   **Proper Requirements:** When assessing if a person is "proper," undertakings must assess their financial soundness and honesty [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0012__guideline-11-fit-requirements]. This assessment is based on relevant evidence of business conduct, personal behaviour, and character, including any supervisory, financial, or criminal aspects regardless of jurisdiction [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0012__guideline-11-fit-requirements].
*   **Policies and Procedures:** National competent authorities should ensure undertakings have a fit and proper policy that includes:
    *   Procedures for assessing the propriety and fitness of those with key functions or who effectively run the undertaking, both on an on-going basis and when being considered for the position [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0014__guideline-13-fit-and-proper-policies-and];
    *   A description of situations that trigger a re-assessment of fit and proper requirements [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0014__guideline-13-fit-and-proper-policies-and];
    *   Internal standards and procedures for assessing other relevant personnel not subject to Article 42 of the Solvency II Directive, both on an on-going basis and when being considered for the position [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0014__guideline-13-fit-and-proper-policies-and].

